    "body": "@nventuro @frangio I gave it a shot. Submitted PR #2243  Here is how one of the functions look for the example you mentioned above. Any chances or adjustments that need to be made please let me know. Thanks!\r\n```\r\n/**\r\n * @dev Returns the downcasted int8 from int256, reverting on\r\n * overflow (when the input is less than smallest int8 or greater \r\n * than largest int8).\r\n *\r\n * Counterpart to Solidity's `int8` operator.\r\n *\r\n * Requirements:\r\n *\r\n * - input must fit into 8 bits.\r\n */ \r\nfunction toInt8(int256 value) internal pure returns (int8) {\r\n    require(value >= -2**7 && value < 2**7, \"SafeCast: value doesn\\'t fit in 8 bits\");\r\n    return int8(value);         \r\n }\r\n```",
